<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-05T21:00:00-05:00" n="1000" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1000">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/58: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-05T22:00:00-04:00">August 5,
                                    1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1101. In view of the extreme delicacy of the questions involved and the
                            necessity of absolute secrecy in regard thereto, please request Colonel
                            Hoskins to refrain entirely from any further discussion of the matter
                            referred to in your 1327, July 27, 9 a.m.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>